To calculate the Net Profit Margin, we use the following formula:

\[ \text{Net Profit Margin} = \left( \frac{\text{Net Profit}}{\text{Total Revenue}} \right) \times 100 \]

From the given problem:
- Net Profit = 112,375.10
- Total Revenue = 775,598.77

Now, plug these values into the formula:

\[ \text{Net Profit Margin} = \left( \frac{112,375.10}{775,598.77} \right) \times 100 \]

\[ \text{Net Profit Margin} \approx 14.49\% \]

So, the solution is:

```json
{"solution": {'Net Profit Margin': '14.49%'} }
```
